Visualizations¶

This code will create a scatter plot visualizing the relationship between 'Total Vaccination Doses' (on the x-axis) and 'Dose 2' (on the y-axis) in the vaccine_backup dataset. Points on the plot will be red, as specified by the c='red' parameter. The title and axis labels provide context for the plot.

plt.scatter(vaccine_backup['Total Vaccination Doses'],vaccine_backup['Dose 2'], c='red')

This code will generate a regression plot with 'Total Vaccination Doses' on the x-axis, 'Dose 1 12-14' on the y-axis, a regression line representing the relationship between the two variables, and asterisk markers for the data points. The plot will have a dark grid background, as specified by the sns.set(style="darkgrid") line.

In [23]:

This code will create an lmplot displaying 'Total Vaccination Doses' on the x-axis, 'Population' on the y-axis, with data points colored based on the values in the 'Dose 1 12-14' column. The legend will indicate the colors corresponding to each unique value in the 'Dose 1 12-14' column. No regression line will be fit to the data points due to fit_reg=False.
